resource.name: Resurface or reconstruct at least 12 miles of City streets per year
resource.description: The City of Janesville continues to invest in our street infrastructure, and has done so by significantly increasing the miles of City streets resurfaced or reconstructed per year since 2014. This goal is measured by tracking the miles of City streets resurfaced or reconstructed per year.

resource.name: Rainy Day Fun Measure
resource.description: This goal is measured by tracking the undesignated General Fund balance as a percentage of General Fund operating expenditures. Council Policy No. 89 requires the City to maintain an undesignated General Fund balance between two and three months (16.7% to 25%) of General Fund operating expenditures.

resource.name: Measuring City of Janesville employees' engagement
resource.description: Organizations with an engaged workforce are often more innovative and productive; have higher employee satisfaction; and recruit and retain good employees. This goal is measured by tracking the percentage of employees engaged per the results of the City of Janesville's Engagement Survey conducted by Wonderlic.

resource.name: Recreation Participants Measure
resource.description: Recreation programs are important for physical and psychological wellbeing as well as offer people a great way to socialize and meet others they would normally not have contact with in their daily lives. This goal is measured by tracking the number of people participating in the City of Janesville's recreation programs.

resource.name: Debt Services Payments
resource.description: This goal is measured by tracking the percentage of General Fund expenditures for debt service payments. City Council Policy No. 75 limits the General Fund's debt service payments to 20% of the General Fund budget.

resource.name: GO Debt below 5% City's EAV
resource.description: This goal is measured by tracking General Obligation (GO) debt as a percentage of the City's equalized assessed value. The State of Wisconsin limits the amount of GO debt issued by a municipality to 5% of its equalized assessed value. Additionally, City Council Policy No. 75 further limits GO debt to 2.5% of the City's equalized assessed value.

resource.name: Rock River Shoreline Measure

resource.name: Maintain the percentage of the City of Janesville's authorized positions filled above 95%
resource.description: The City of Janesville's ability to provide the municipal programs and services that our residents, businesses, and visitors expect is driven by having a quality and reliable workforce. This goal is measured by tracking the percentage of the City’s authorized positions filled.
